ALCOHOL CONTAMINATION, FATAL - RUSSIA (10)
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1] Irkutsk
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail Corr.VM <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regnum [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/733206.html>

78 people are hospitalized with toxic hepatitis in Irkutsk
-----------------------------------------------
Since the beginning of the alcohol epidemic, around 3 Nov 2006, 1233
people applied for care due to alcohol poisoning. Currently, 983
people are in the hospital with toxic hepatitis. In the previous 2
days, 78 people were admitted to the hospital. The only day without a
fatal case in Irkutsk was 2 Nov 2006. The present death toll in
Irkutsk has reached 40.
[Map at
<http://www.cnn.com/SPECIALS/2000/russia/story/train/lake.baikal/trans.siberia.map.gif>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[2] Arkhangelsk
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail Corr.VM <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Strana [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://www.strana.ru/news/297212.html>

83 people poisoned in Arkhangelsk with alcohol
-----------------------------------------------
One of the 83 people admitted with poisoning has died. All patients
were hospitalized with the diagnosis of toxic hepatitis. The majority
are elderly and unemployed. All of them had been drinking
non-reliable alcohol bought in the market.
[Map at <http://www.touch.expo2005.ru/files/map/region/ARKHANGELSK_REGION.gif>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[3] Belgorod
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: FvbNfss [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://www.ami-tass.ru/article/16297.html>

945 total in Belgorod registered with poisoning
-----------------------------------------------
Of the 945 hospitalized people, 48 have died. So far, 738 diagnosed
with toxic hepatitis have been discharged from the hospital.
Treatment for each person cost 28 000 rubles [approximately USD 1050 - Mod.TG].
[Map at <http://www.touch.expo2005.ru/files/map/region/BELGOROD_REGION.gif>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[4] Saratov
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regions [translated by Mod NR, edited]
<http://www.regions.ru/news/2024040>

6 people dead in Saratov as a result of alcohol poisoning
-----------------------------------------------
6 people have died in Saratov as a result of alcohol poisoning; 16
more people were admitted to the hospital yesterday [2 Nov 2006]. 205
cases of alcohol poisoning have been registered since the beginning
of the epidemic. 170 of them were diagnosed with toxic hepatitis and
17 people were discharged.
[Map at <http://www.emeraldcityrotary.org/c4w/images/saratov.gif>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[5] Tambov
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ami Tass [translated by Mod NR, edited]
<http://www.ami-tass.ru/article/16281.html>

One person died and 41 are hospitalized in Tambov
-----------------------------------------------
The majority of the cases are registered in Michurinsk city, where 36
people have been admitted to the hospital. According to the
physicians, people were poisoned with technical alcohol, "Troyar,"
meant for cleaning furniture or windows or for use as a disinfectant,
etc. [Map at <http://www.touch.expo2005.ru/files/map/region/TAMBOV_REGION.gif>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
