[7] Volgograd
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Kavkaz.memo.ru [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://kavkaz.memo.ru/newstext/news/id/1103140.html>

Cases are rising in Volgograd
---------------------------------
The number of cases in Volgograd has reached 196. All of the patients
have been diagnosed with toxic hepatitis. A 32-year-old man has died
as a result of poisoning. The cause of death, according to pathology,
was necrosis of the liver.
[Map at
<http://content.answers.com/main/content/wp/en/9/94/Map_european_russia_volgograd.png>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[8] Vologda
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Trasnlit [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://www.transmit.ru/news/2006/11/3/403>

Cases in Vologda
-------------------
5 people have died, and 162 are still in the hospital. The alcohol
epidemic does not seem to have peaked yet on a countrywide basis.
About 200 people were hospitalized with alcohol poisoning; 5 people
have died as a result of liver necrosis. So far, the lives of 5 more
people are in danger as well. Physicians are forecasting an increase
in the death toll.
[Map at <http://www.touch.expo2005.ru/files/map/region/VOLOGDA_REGION.gif>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[9] Yakutiya
Date: 3 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regnum.ru [translated by Mod NR, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/733448.html>

125 people are poisoned in Yakutiya
-----------------------------------------
125 people have been poisoned in Yakutiya as a result of technical
alcohol use. Most of the people say that this is associated with the
new policy requirements on alcohol. At the same time, people were
poisoned with so called alcohol substitutes. Out of 125 hospitalized,
one was a 14-year-old teenager and 27 were women with an age range of 27 to 68.
[Map at
<http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/Laboratory/Biome/Images/maprussia.jpgas>]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Since the new policy on alcohol excise taxes was introduced,
production companies have switched from using technical alcohol to
isopropyl alcohol that is 1000 times more poisonous. The 2nd thing
that has contributed to a rise in the epidemic was the prohibition of
imports of Georgian and Ukrainian wines to Russia. - Corr.VM]
